The paper deals with recursion schemes, which are a topic in theoretical computer science and formal language theory. The use of non-deterministic recursion schemes and their ability to recognize languages of finite trees suggests a connection to formal language theory and automata theory, which are covered in cs.FL and cs.THEORY. The paper also discusses the decidability of the diagonal problem, which is a topic in logic and computability theory, suggesting a connection to cs.LO. The algorithmic aspects of the paper, such as computing the downward closure of languages and its application to reachability analysis, suggest a connection to cs.PL and cs.DS.
